=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_FBSineN_ex4 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_bright mixed sound, with fm_or_inharmonic oscillator character around 1405 Hz, featuring punchy attack and compressed envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally dense.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_bright
  crest_factor_db: compressed
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: mixed
  spectral_complexity_mean: dense
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 1405.0076
  harmonic_decay_rate: 0.5911
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5005
  pitch_clarity: 21.9318
  inharmonicity: 0.2202
  type: fm_or_inharmonic
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -4.3255
  resonance_freq: 5254.1016

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: FBSineN Example 4
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/FBSineN.html
// Tags: FBSineN, Classes, oscillator
// ---
// --- Example 4 ---
// increase phase multiplier
{ FBSineN.ar(SampleRate.ir, 1, 0, XLine.kr(1, 2, 10), 0.1) * 0.2 }.play(s);
